## Blocks

### 4. `m3d-globe`
Elabore 3d interactive globe with terrain continents and data markers.
Content format: Inline, DAM Path, Upload as usual going to DAM or sheet. 
`label,lat,lon,value` lines (one per row).
Upload supports CSV, txt, PDF
- Sphere with wireframe overlay (`THREE.WireframeGeometry`). Subtle auto-rotation.
- Textures for multicolor terrain snow-capped mountains light green plains
- Exceptional ocean rendering, moving animated even responds a bit turbulently
- Markers: small `THREE.SphereGeometry` pins placed at lat/lon positions.
- Color and size of pin driven by `value` (normalized 0-1 scale).
- Drag to rotate, scroll to zoom. Click marker shows label in DOM tooltip.
- Default color scheme field: `blue` | `green` | `amber` | `purple`.
- Draw great looking accurate continents, subtle pro lighting and textures
- Globe spins slowlly on proper tilted earth-axis with pole visible by default
- Spinning stops on hover/entry then globe can be spun around and data points
- Clicking points opens detail panels on click with nearest city, label and value
- Points use 3d shapes chosen by the author or random sensible ones based on quick
analysis of the data subject or a default set that looks great

